      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "You don't need to buy everything at once. The beauty of Xiaomi CL is that each device works standalone but gets better as you add more. Here's how I'd approach it:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Start with a smartphone if...",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "You want a daily driver with flagship specs at mid-range pricing. The Xiaomi 17T Pro caught my attention recently: Leica 5x telephoto lens, 7000mAh battery (that's two full days for most people), and a display that rivals phones costing twice as much. It runs HyperOS, which means seamless integration with every other Xiaomi device you add later.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Start with a wearable if...",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Fitness tracking is your priority. The Smart Band line delivers heart rate monitoring, SpO2 tracking, sleep analysis, and workout detection — features that competitors charge $200+ for. I wore mine for three weeks straight, and the battery lasted 11 days. Not hours. *Days.*",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Start with smart home if...",
            "marks": []
          }
